<title>The<i> !ho</i></title>
<summary><i>In a peculiar state of the atmosphere, in which sounds can be heard at a considerable distance, sitting, instead of standing, is recommended; for fear of evil consequences. Standing over those who are sitting, on account of its injurious effects, is also objected to, etc. In the Katkop dialect, by Díä!kwãin (L V.-20. 5559 rev.-5568 rev.).</i> The <i>!ho </i>can kill people who are standing over visitors and sticks can &apos;seek people&apos; and &apos;strike&apos; them dead if they stand still. If a person&apos;s teeth are &apos;above&apos; or over their &apos;knees&apos; they are standing over other people and can cause their deaths or make them ill.  </summary><comments>1) See also <i>The !kho: a blue mist which resembles smoke </i>and <i>The !ho and Ko-boken, </i>2) This story is found in Book V-20</comments><date>20 November 1875 (started)</date><storypages>5559v-5568v</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><category>Celestial bodies and aeroscopy</category><author>Dia!kwain (David Hoesar) (V)</author><keyword><kw>standing</kw><subkw>&apos;teeth over knees&apos;</subkw></keyword>
